         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 10 of Aurelius Antoninus Caesar the lord Armeniacus Medicus Parthicus maximus, Pharmouthi 9 on account of Phamenoth. Paid by Sarapias and Chairemon alias Longus for pasture-tax of the tenth year for (the district) Thesmophoriou a hundred and eight drachmai, total 108 and (the fee) for the receipt.</ab>
